    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Psalms",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 149,
        "summary": "Praise the Lord in the congregation of the Saints\u2014He will beautify the meek with salvation.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Praise ye the Lord. Sing unto the Lord a new song, and his praise in the congregation of saints.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Saints.",
                        "start": 89,
                        "end": 95
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Let Israel rejoice in him that made him: let the children of Zion be joyful in their King.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 95:6.",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Joel 2:23; D&C 84:56.",
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 65
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 5:50.",
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 89
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Let them praise his name in the dance: let them sing praises unto him with the timbrel and harp.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For the Lord taketh pleasure in his people: he will beautify the meek with salvation.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Beauty.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Let the saints be joyful in glory: let them sing aloud upon their beds.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Glory.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 33
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Singing.",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 48
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 63:6.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Let the high praises of God be in their mouth, and a twoedged sword in their hand;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 6:2.",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 61
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 30
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "To execute vengeance upon the heathen, and punishments upon the people;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 42
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "To bind their kings with chains, and their nobles with fetters of iron;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "To execute upon them the judgment written: this honour have all his saints. Praise ye the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}